result.text:
1/ We previously raised questions about the massive funding round—one of the biggest of 2025—that metaverse-turned-AI firm #Napster announced as a done deal in January. The money is never coming, the company said Thursday. 

-- Its spokesperson told @Forbes in March the money was in “an Infinite Reality [the company's name at the time] account and is available to us” and that they were “actively leveraging” it. (For this story, she wrote that the statements “were made in good faith based on what we understood at the time. We have since uncovered indications of misconduct that suggest the information provided to us then was not accurate.") 
-- The company raised additional funds (not as part of a funding round) and made stock-based acquisitions after announcing the round.
-- The SEC and DOJ are looking into things; the company is not a target of the latter investigation.
 
Read the story, from @_IainMartin and me (link in comment as well):

https://t.co/mvZnJUd6E6
